# =============================================================
# Docker build-context exclusions
# =============================================================
# Build context is the repo root (so service Dockerfiles can COPY
# from both shared/ and services/). Without this file, the entire
# repo would be sent to the daemon for every build.
# =============================================================

# Build output
**/target/

# IDE
**/.idea/
**/*.iml
**/.vscode/

# Git + GitHub
.git/
.github/

# OS
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# Maven
**/.mvn/wrapper/maven-wrapper.jar

# Secrets / overrides — never bake these into images
.env
.env.local
**/application-local.yml
**/application-secret.yml

# Things the build doesn't need
monolith-reference/
postman/
docs/
docker/
MIGRATION_LOG.md
README.md
